task.summary: Default task
Better unicode support, close https://github.com/jeancroy/fuzzaldrin-plus/issues/10

Add a cache for prepared query.
Helps offset the slowdown caused by more complex unicode uppercase.

Allow a query made entirely of optional character.
Test for 0 length query in fuzzaldrin module. But do not retest 0 length on core string.

Use more strict start / end of word boundary, help reduce number of comparisons
Start of word (strict): Match follow a separator or is Capital in camelCase.
Start of word (loose): Strict Or match is a separator.
In acronym test, only test once for being a separator
Make parameters of private scorer.score required
Make extension bonus optional
Remove legacy flag Use npm version of classic fuzzaldrin to do benchmark
Build a minified browserify version on publish
Remove dependecy on path module. pathSeparator now computed from process.platform==win32 pathSeparator can also be specified by option hash to pass everythin to prepQuery.
Add an interactive demo
Simplified signature: prepQuery now part of the option hash as preparedQuery. Added method fuzzaldrin.wrap, updated demo to use it Extension bonus now disabled by default.
Reorganize code - extracted pathScorer & query module from large scorer module - unified usage of option hash from main fuzzaldrin module - logic for wrap & match moved back to matcher module
Reorganize code - extracted pathScorer & query module from large scorer module - unified usage of option hash from main fuzzaldrin module - logic for wrap & match moved back to matcher module
fix #25
handle undefined process #31
setup bower
Translate to es6, build using gulp+babel+webpack
fix bower release
